      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "1t was rumored today that the\nFreeman's Labor Journal has pass\ned into new hands and the report\nhas been practically confirmed by\nthose prominently connected with\nthe trades council.\n\n\n1t is not known who are the ac-\ntual purchasers of the paper, but it\nis said that George Wright of the\nAmerican Type Founders company\nis promoting the deal.\n\n\nThe sale will cause the discontin-\nuance of the hostile attitude to-\nwards the Journal by the trades\ncouncil."
    }
  ]
